div.p:
The King hath done his part in calling Parliaments often, for which he is to be thanked;
except it can be made evident it was his fault that they were of no longer continuance:
so far from that, it is plain these men who complain have been so much the
cause of the late Dissolutions, that one would swear they designed to provoke the King
to them, and that he hath had in these cases so much patience, he can hardly answer it
to the Nation, whose peace he is entrusted with and bound to preserve.
